class StockSpanner {
public:
    StockSpanner() {}

    int next(int price) {
        int prevPrice = INT_MAX;
        int span = 0;
        if (price <= prevPrice) {
            span++;
        }
        prevPrice = price;
        return span;
    }
};
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

The algorithm maintains two variables: prevPrice and span. It checks if the current price is less than or equal to the previous price. If it is, the span is incremented. Then, it updates the prevPrice to the current price. This approach has a time complexity of O(1) because the algorithm only performs a constant number of operations for each input price. The space complexity is also O(1) because the algorithm only uses a constant amount of space to store the prevPrice and span variables. The energy implications are low because the algorithm does not involve any energy-consuming operations.

